We note that if $a>2$, then $a / b \leq 5 / 3$, and if $a>5$, then $a / b \leq 3 / 2$. If $a_{1}>2$, then $\frac{a_{1}}{b_{1}} \cdot \frac{a_{2}}{\sigma_{2}} \cdot \frac{a_{1}}{b_{1}}<(5 / 3)^{3}<5$, a contradiction. Hence $a_{1}=2$. If also $a_{2}=2$, then $a_{3} / b_{3}=5 / 4 \leq \sqrt[3]{2}$, which is impossible. Also, if $a_{2} \geq 6$, then $\frac{a_{2}}{b_{2}} \cdot \frac{a_{3}}{b_{3}} \leq(1.5)^{2}<2.5$, again a contradiction. We thus have the following cases:
(i) $a_{1}=2, a_{2}=3$, then $a_{3} / b_{3}=5 / 3$, which holds only if $a_{3}=5$;
(ii) $a_{1}=2, a_{2}=4$, then $a_{3} / b_{3}=15 / 8$, which is impossible;
(iii) $a_{1}=2, a_{2}=5$, then $a_{3} / b_{3}=3 / 2$, which holds only if $a_{3}=6$.

